                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Canon_Class_Lat_112-item5a">
                     <locus from="61v">(fol. 61v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_163502301">Marchetto da Padova</author>
                     <title key="work_3077">Aue regina / Mater innocencie / Ite missa est</title>
                     <note>A three-part motet to the Blessed Virgin in Italian Ars nova notation, in which an acrostic refers to Marcus Paduanus. Although not definitely in the hand of the main scribe this is contemporary with the main text. On it see RISM, sér. B, pt. 4, vol. iv (1972), 666. </note>
